article.headline: Austin Peay 108, Berea 53
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Corey Arentsen and Anthony Campbell scored 20 points apiece to help hot-shooting Austin Peay rout NAIA's Berea 108-53 Wednesday night. Travis Beltran chipped in 16 points, Chris Horton 15, and Will Triggs had 11 for Austin Peay (6-4), which hit 38 of 67 shot attempts from the field. Arentsen made 6 of 8 3-pointers for the Governors, who made 12 of 26 treys as a team and shot over 40 percent from deep for the third time this season. Arentsen's 3-pointer with 12:19 left in the second half put Austin Peay up 75-32. Campbell and Arentsen saw just 19 and 22 minutes of action, as 14 different Austin Peay players logged minutes, with 11 of them scoring. Berea (6-5) was led by 13 points from Koty Riley and 11 from Dominique Garmon, but the Mountaineers shot just 32.8 percent (21 of 64) from the field.
